This provides persistent access to Mantine component documentation, hooks, and styling guides, comprehensive UI spacing best practices, and React design patterns for the AcousticCanvas audio analysis workspace.

## Code Style

- Write junior-friendly code: simple, flat, and easy to follow — no clever abstractions
- Use long, descriptive names for variables, functions, and components that make intent obvious without needing comments
- Avoid one-liners, nested ternaries, and complex chaining — prefer explicit steps
- Keep functions short and single-purpose; if a function does two things, split it
- All React components must be declared as `export const ComponentName = (): JSX.Element => {` — always const arrow functions, never `function` declarations
- Always use `import type { JSX } from 'react'` at the top of every `.tsx` file — never import the default React object
- Import other React types explicitly: e.g. `import type { JSX, ReactNode } from 'react'`

## Feature Folder Structure (Vertical Slice Architecture)

Every feature lives in `src/features/<featureName>/` and must follow this structure:

```
src/features/<featureName>/
  hooks/        # React hooks specific to this feature (e.g. useManualPlayback.ts)
  services/     # API call functions for this feature (e.g. manualAnalysisService.ts)
  utils/        # Pure helper functions for this feature (e.g. formatDuration.ts)
  <FeatureName>.tsx          # Root component
  <FeatureName>.module.scss  # Scoped styles
```

- `hooks/` — custom React hooks only; no JSX, no API calls
- `services/` — functions that call backend endpoints; no React, no JSX
- `utils/` — pure functions with no side effects; no React, no API calls
- Never put backend logic or data transformation in components — delegate to `services/` or `utils/`
- When creating a new feature, always scaffold all three folders (use `.gitkeep` if empty)

## Architecture: Frontend vs Backend

- All logic, calculations, and data transformations belong in the backend — no exceptions
- The frontend only renders what the backend returns; it does not compute, derive, or transform data
- No DSP, audio math, signal processing, or analysis of any kind in the frontend
- No business rules or domain decisions in the frontend
- Frontend responsibilities: display state, handle user input, call backend endpoints, render results
